author: COMSOL
description: A magnetic material in the core of an inductor influences the inductance. If the magnetic material is nonlinear the inductance depends on the current through the inductor. This example analyzes the small-signal behavior of an inductance with a nonlinear core, and investigates how the small-signal inductance depends on the DC current.
label: small_signal_analysis_of_inductor.mph
